      "message": "I\u0027ll tell you what: if, after we have a few more non-test implementations, we find that we want a base class, we can consider it then.\n\nI\u0027m not convinced because what you\u0027re proposing seems like it\u0027d require subclasses to call the base class implementation, which is extra work that it\u0027s very easy to forget to do. You could devise an alternative where the public interface was nonvirtual and it delegated to private internal interface methods, but that seems like overkill for the task at hand.",
